        <hr class="separator" style="margin-top: 5px" />

        <div style="padding-left: 20px;">
            <div class="">
                <img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/thunderclap-production/campaigns/organizer_images/000/003/926/original/stringio.txt?1378746094" class="left" alt="profile image" width="60" height="60" />

                <div class="organizer_info">
                    <div style="font-weight: 600;">Human Rights at FCO</div>
                        <div><a href="https://twitter.com/FCOHumanRights">@FCOHumanRights</a></div>
                    <!-- <div>Created this on Sep 09, 2013</div> -->
                </div>

                <div style="height: 15px">&nbsp;</div>
                <div class="clear"></div>
            </div>

            <div class="half_spacer"></div>

            <div class="organizer_right">
                <script>!function(d,s,id){var js,fjs=d.getElementsByTagName(s)[0];if(!d.getElementById(id)){js=d.createElement(s);js.id=id;js.src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js";fjs.parentNode.insertBefore(js,fjs);}}(document,"script","twitter-wjs");</script>

                <div class="summary" style="width: 255px; border: 0; padding: 0;">The UK Government is calling for international action to address the problem of sexual violence in conflict.<br /><br />The Preventing Sexual Violence Initiative was launched by UK Foreign Secretary William Hague and UN Special Envoy for Refugees Angelina Jolie in 2012. It is working to replace the culture of impunity for sexual violence committed in conflict with one of deterrence - by increasing the number of perpetrators brought to justice both internationally and nationally; by strengthening international efforts and co-ordination to prevent and respond to sexual violence; and by supporting states to build their national capacity. #TimetoAct</div>
            </div>
